  "text": "Among the different studies described in the literature, the effect of liposomal inclusion on the stability and in vitro antiherpetic activity of Santolina insularis L. (Asteraceae) essential oil was very remarkable. Pure essential oil cannot be use topically because of its high volatility and enhancer penetration properties, which can result in safety concerns, hence, a suitable formulation should be prepared. Liposomes successfully prevented its degradation and were effective in inactivating HSV-1, and that activity is principally due to direct virucidal effects [CITATION_1] .",
